The commissioner shall not approve the acquisition if the commissioner finds that:
The requirements of KRS 304.37-120(4)(a) have not been satisfied;
The acquisition will frustrate the fair and equitable plan of conversion as approved by the members and the commissioner;
The acquisition or change of control will result in unjust enrichment of the acquiring persons to the detriment of the eligible members of the converting mutual; and
The acquisition would not be in the best interest of the present and future policyholders of the former mutual, without regard to any interest of policyholders as shareholders of the former mutual or any affiliate company.
